flowRoot.flowPara: RDF schema for the odML data model

text.tspan: To easily store, select, retrieve and share data using an open
format we provide the NIX format, which offers convenient
organization of data and metadata, supporting various data
types including electrophysiology and imaging, and enables to
effectively link data and corresponding analysis results as well
as the associated metadata. NIX builds on the odML metadata
format and is supported by the Neo Python package for electro-
physiology, enabling Neo users to store their data in a common
open format. Export of odML data to RDF opens the format to
Accessing and managing data from multiple workplaces

from within or outside the lab is even more demanding.
